A. CMOS-Based Boolean Embedding Circuit
The mapping of a Boolean embedding matrix can eliminate
the usage of multipliers. For a {0, 1}mÃ—n Boolean embedding
matrix, the MAC only accumulate signal data when Boolean
multiplicand is 1. For a more general {âˆ’1, 1}mÃ—n Boolean matrix, the Boolean multiplicand indicates addition or subtraction
for the signal data. That is to say, the required resources of fulladders are only linearly depending on the precision of signal Î©x.
As such, the hardware resource can be significantly reduced.
Specifically for the {âˆ’1, 1}mÃ—n embedding matrix mapping,
the multiplication by âˆ’1 requires the calculation of 2â€™s complement. The intuitive approach is illustrated in Fig. 4(b). The

